I saw him Dean/ St Mary's.   In Janesville Wisconsin.|He is polite and theoretically knowledgeable and patient but to a certain extent. I think he just needs to understand that most of his patients see him because they have been having chronic and severe pains and also after they have exhausted other options. I really appreciate how he made sure I understood  the proposed treatment. It's sensitive ... just be empathetic and scientific at the same time and don't jump into conclusion about the patient's personality when the treatment doesn't work.|Like another reviewer said, very respectful and caring doctor. After my initial consultation with him I was 100% confident that he was going to help me handle my chronic pain, and he has done wonders for me so far. I highly recommend him if you're looking for trigger point injections.|Very respectful and caring doctor.  He has shown me respect and dignity which is hard to find sometimes as a chronic pain patient.  If you are honest with him he will be very open to ideas.  I don't know where I would be without him.|Dr Achampong is a great doctor. He has improved the quality of my life. He has spent considerable time with me in clinic discussing various options. Pain management is an important service for the management of chronic pain. Dr Achampong works really well with the other members of my medical team. He is respectful and open to patient ideas. Pain management is more than the prescription of opioids; pain psychology and physical therapy are an integral part of the coping process. I highly recommend this doctor.|He is an amazing doctor who knows what he is doing. From all the doctors he is the only one who found the issue my friend has and suggeated the correct combination of treatments which are working! Thank you Dr. A|Varry rude told me to go blank myself amazing nothing about this and i reported him|Highly recommend
